                        <!-- Project Description -->
                        <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" FontSize="16" Foreground="#4A5568" Margin="0,10" TextAlignment="Center">
                            The AI-Driven Solar Energy Management System is an innovative solution designed to optimize the performance and reliability of solar energy installations using the power of artificial intelligence and predictive analytics. As the world transitions toward renewable energy, managing solar systems efficiently is critical to maximizing energy yield, reducing downtime, and minimizing operational costs.

                            This project leverages machine learning models to predict solar power generation based on historical weather data, panel performance metrics, and environmental factors. These predictions enable users and operators to plan energy usage, storage, and grid interaction more effectively.

                            In addition to forecasting, the system includes fault detection algorithms capable of identifying anomalies and potential failures in solar inverters or panels before they cause significant power loss. These insights allow for proactive maintenance, reducing equipment downtime and extending the lifespan of the infrastructure.

                            The solution is implemented as a user-friendly desktop application that visualizes energy trends, weather patterns, system health status, and prediction results through interactive charts and data views. Users can upload or fetch datasets (e.g., CSV weather or energy logs), which are processed using AI pipelines running locally.

                            By integrating data science, software development, and renewable energy expertise, this project demonstrates how digital intelligence can transform sustainable energy systems into smarter, more reliable assets.
                        </TextBlock>
